<br>
This is possible within limits, but does not have a dramatic effect at the stage of the game that Mebe plays in. The truth is that most items have a pretty good mix of AC and stamina and that item scarcity is as likely to determine items used as choice. Can item selection spend some of the AC bonus to get more HP? Sure. Can item selection allow Mebe to lower AC to the softcap and gain as much STA as a similiarly geared ogre warrior? Mebe does not think so. <br>
<br>
Fully buffed Mebe hits 1401 AC but still is more than 50 away from max STA with full raid buffs. That's 150 points over the softcap. An ogre warrior without the 40ish AC bonus would be at 1360AC, still well above the softcap and with just as much flexibility to trade AC for HP and STA gear.<br>
<br>
The AC softcap strongly diminishes the value of the extra AC in the early high end game for a class who's quest armor takes you well over the AC softcap anyway. Ironically, lower AC gear for iksars diminishes the value of the AC bonus in the low end game. There does seem to be a sweet spot for iksar in the middle of the game as you pass into PoG and Thurg armor and before you hit the AC softcap by leveling / moving to Kael/SS armor. Perhaps if you are iksar in NToV gear, the view changes again since the AC cap is a soft cap (after all, it is 4 real AC) and the STA cap is a hard one. At that point it becomes 4 real AC and regen vs. unstunnability.<br>
<br>
Just Mebe's opinion.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 4:18:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1273.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE: High End Race Issues</span><hr size=1> The best race for a warrior is the one you enjoy playing.  If being an ogre makes you happy, thats what you should place.  If you like a halfling or a wood elf, play that.<br>
<br>
Yes perhaps this or that stat makes a small difference here or there.  But ultimately it is really more the skill of the player and the quality of the gear that makes the difference, not one race or another.  And many of the disadvantages you get with one race or advantages you get with another can be adjusted for with the right gear.<br>
<br>
Sure people can over analyze the variations between the races until they are blue in the face.  But if you don't enjoy what you play, whats the point?<br>
<br>
So my advice would be go play the race you enjoy.  Learn all you can about playing your class well.  Get the best gear you can scrounge up and have fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 4:19:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1273.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE: High End Race Issues</span><hr size=1> The best race for a warrior is the one you enjoy playing.  If being an ogre makes you happy, thats what you should place.  If you like a halfling or a wood elf, play that.<br>
